news.title: Thirteen of 100 smart cities have completed all their projects: Centre
news.para: In a written reply to a question, Union Minister of State for Housing and Urban Affairs Tokhan Sahu said more than 84,000 CCTV surveillance cameras have been installed and 713 kilometres of cycle tracks developed in 100 smart cities so far.

news.title: Housing ministry spends Rs 2.3 crore per month on consultants
news.para: The ministry spends around Rs 2.3 crore per month to pay salaries to these outsourced manpower, with some of them taking home between Rs 2.5 lakh to Rs 5 lakh, as per the details submitted by the ministry to Rajya Sabha.

news.title: Delhi LG approves redevelopment of slum areas under Jahan Jhuggi Wahin Makaan scheme
news.para: The modification in policy will allow projects to be more viable and more players could come forward for in-situ slum projects and thereby more houses could be built, officials said.

news.title: Consortium aims to take ESR Group private, valuing it at over $7 billion: Sources
news.para: Warburg Pincus, ESR's top shareholder with a 14% stake, plans to roll over its holdings into the future private company, rather than cash out, said the two sources and two other people with knowledge of the matter.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh govt launches hi-tech township near Jewar International Airport
news.para: The ambitious project by Yamuna Expressway Industrial Development Authority (YEIDA) is situated in Sector-24A of Noida, one kilometre from the International Film City, 500 metres from the Yamuna Expressway and close to the MotoGP track, an official statement issued here said.

news.title: High court stays clearance for 12-villa project at Paliem in Bardez
news.para: The petition challenges the technical clearance order granted for the construction in an orchard area with a no-development slope.

news.title: Investors can get co-developer status in GIFT SEZ commercial projects in Gujarat
news.para: ​​This opportunity emerged after the Union minister of commerce granted approval to an investor's application for co-developer status in GIFT SEZ's commercial tower Pragya, which houses the IFSC Authority headquarters and was developed by Savvy Group.

news.title: Haryana RERA mandates builders to submit annual reports within 30 days
news.para: The move comes after the regulator observed widespread non-compliance by promoters, raising concerns about transparency and accountability in the sector.

news.title: K Raheja Investment pays Rs 68.73 lakh to settle REIT norms violation case with Sebi
news.para: Mindspace Business Parks REIT, sponsored by K Raheja Corp group, was listed on the Indian bourses in August 2020. It owns office portfolios in the Mumbai Region, Pune, Hyderabad, and Chennai.

news.title: Heidelberg Materials acquires US firm Giant Cement for $600 million
news.para: "The acquisition ... will further strengthen our cement footprint in the growing Southeastern U.S. and New England markets," said Chris Ward, CEO of Heidelberg Materials North America.

news.title: Over 53,480 acres of government land under encroachment in Odisha: Minister
news.para: In response to a query by BJD legislator Arun Kumar Sahoo, the minister said, "In accordance with the Odisha Prevention of Land Encroachment (OPLE) Act, 1972, the removal of encroachments on government land is an ongoing process."

news.title: Telangana Bhoodan board issues eviction notices over alleged illegal transactions
news.para: The move followed a report by Enforcement Directorate, which was submitted to the director general of police under the Prevention of Money Laundering Act.

news.title: Telangana HC orders eviction of encroachments for Musi riverfront project
news.para: In a recent order, the court issued several directions while disposing of a batch of writ petitions challenging the action of the government wings of making efforts to demolish residential houses.

news.title: Pending home sales in USA rise 2% in October 2024
news.para: The National Association of Realtors (NAR) said on Wednesday its Pending Home Sales Index, based on signed contracts, rose 2.0% last month to 77.4 - the highest since March - from 75.9 in September.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh govt proposes new policy to fast track bulk land allotment
news.para: The move is linked to the state's decision to come up with Foreign Direct Investment (FDI) Policy-2023 and the Incentive Policy for Fortune-500 Companies' Investments 2023 in place.

news.title: MCD imposes Rs 95.35 lakh fine for illegal dumping C&D waste in October 2024
news.para: The NGT sought regular replies from the authorities concerned with steps preventing air pollution in the national capital.

news.title: Real estate and offshore betting sectors lead in advertising complaints: Report
news.para: Realty (34%), illegal betting (29%), healthcare (8%), personal care (7%), and food & beverage (6%) featured as the top five categories with the highest code violations.

news.title: Gujarat: Swastika Overseas defrauded of 2.38 crore by importer and shipping sub-agent
news.para: Kapil Goriya, who runs Swastika Overseas, a Morbi-based ceramics trading company, travelled to Dubai to confront the importer but to no avail. He filed a complaint at B Division police station in Morbi in June.

news.title: Kolkata's first metro link to airport set to be ready by March 2025
news.para: The Noapara-Airport is the Phase I of Yellow Line, which will eventually link Barasat with Kolkata.

news.title: Office leasing by global capability centres in Chennai to reach 3.2 million sq ft by 2025: Report
news.para: Chennai has witnessed GCC office absorption increasing from 1.4 million sq ft in 2022 to 2.3 million sq ft in the first nine months of 2024.
